negotiator.session

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • negotiator.session.Session

  • public class Session
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores runtime info around a session. Mainly the rounds info. A Session consists of Rounds with in turn consists of Turn. From this session object some information about the current negotiation can be extracted. Important is the startNewRound(Round) method which is used to add a new round to the session. At this moment (05-08-2014) adding new rounds to the session is the responsibility of the SessionManager.
    Author:
    David Festen

      • Session

        public Session(Deadline deadlines,
               SessionsInfo info)
        Create a new instance of the session object. This should normally only happen once every session. See also the class documentation of Session. This also creates a timeline that starts running the moment Session is created.
        Parameters:
        deadlines - Map of deadline constraints
        info - the global SessionsInfo

    • Method Detail

      • getDeadlines

        public Deadline getDeadlines()
        Gets the deadline constraints
        Returns:
        a map of deadline types and values

      • startTimer

        public void startTimer()
        Updates the timestamp of this Session. Use just before starting the negotiation for most accurate timing. Timing is used in for example time deadline constraints. But might also be used in log messages as well as statistics.

      • stopTimer

        public void stopTimer()
        Updates the timestamp of this Session. Use just after finish the negotiation for most accurate timing. Timing is used in for example time deadline constraints. But might also be used in log messages as well as statistics. If you need to manually set it, consider using the setRuntimeInNanoSeconds(long) function.

      • getRounds

        public java.util.List<Round> getRounds()
        Gets the rounds currently in this session. When startNewRound(Round) is called a new round will be added. Each round already includes all its Turns, but some turns might not yet been done.
        Returns:
        list of rounds. Can be empty.

      • getMostRecentRound

        public Round getMostRecentRound()
        Get the most recent round.
        Returns:
        The last round of the getRounds() method, or null if no round has been done yet.

      • startNewRound

        public void startNewRound(Round round)
        Add a round to this session. Make sure it contains all the turns necessary to execute the rounds. Normally the new round will be created by using MultilateralProtocol.getRoundStructure(java.util.List, Session)
        Parameters:
        round - The round to add to this session.
